><head><title>glutSolidCone</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" type="text/css"/><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.59.1"/><link rel="home" href="index.xml" title="PyOpenGL 2.0.1.09 Man Pages"/><link rel="up" href="reference-GLUT.xml" title="GLUT"/><link rel="previous" href="glutShowWindow.3GLUT.xml" title="glutShowWindow"/><link rel="next" href="glutSolidCube.3GLUT.xml" title="glutSolidCube"/></head><body bgcolor="white" text="black" link="#0000FF" vlink="#840084" alink="#0000FF"><div class="navheader"><table width="100%" summary="Navigation header"><tr><th colspan="3" align="center">glutSolidCone</th></tr><tr><td width="20%" align="left"><a accesskey="p" href="glutShowWindow.3GLUT.xml">Prev</a> </td><th width="60%" align="center">GLUT</th><td width="20%" align="right"> <a accesskey="n" href="glutSolidCube.3GLUT.xml">Next</a></td></tr></table><hr/></div><div class="refentry" lang="en"><a name="glutSolidCone.3GLUT"/><div class="titlepage"/><div class="refnamediv"><a name="glutSolidCone.3GLUT-name"/><h2>Name</h2><p>glutSolidCone, glutWireCone &#8212; render a solid or wireframe cone respectively.</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><a name="glutSolidCone.3GLUT-c_spec"/><h2>C Specification</h2><table class="funcprototype" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><code>void <tt>glutSolidCone</tt></code></td><td valign="top"><code>(</code></td><td valign="top"><code>GLdouble <i><tt>base</tt></i>, GLdouble <i><tt>height</tt></i>, GLint <i><tt>slices</tt></i>, GLint <i><tt>stacks</tt></i>);</code></td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><code>void <tt>glutWireCone</tt></code></td><td valign="top"><code>(</code></td><td valign="top"><code>GLdouble <i><tt>base</tt></i>, GLdouble <i><tt>height</tt></i>, GLint <i><tt>slices</tt></i>, GLint <i><tt>stacks</tt></i>);</code></td></tr></table></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><a name="glutSolidCone.3GLUT-python_spec"/><h2>Python Specification</h2><table class="funcprototype" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><code><tt>glutSolidCone</tt></code></td><td valign="top"><code>(</code></td><td valign="top"><code><i><tt>base</tt></i>, <i><tt>height</tt></i>, <i><tt>slices</tt></i>, <i><tt>stacks</tt></i>) &#8594; <tt>None</tt></code></td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><code><tt>glutWireCone</tt></code></td><td valign="top"><code>(</code></td><td valign="top"><code><i><tt>base</tt></i>, <i><tt>height</tt></i>, <i><tt>slices</tt></i>, <i><tt>stacks</tt></i>) &#8594; <tt>None</tt></code></td></tr></table></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glutSolidCone.3GLUT-parameters"/><h2>Parameters</h2><div class="variablelist"><dl><dt><span class="term"><i><tt>base</tt></i></span></dt><dd>
						The radius of the base of the cone.
					</dd><dt><span class="term"><i><tt>height</tt></i></span></dt><dd>
						The height of the cone.
					</dd><dt><span class="term"><i><tt>slices</tt></i></span></dt><dd>
						The number of subdivisions around the Z axis.
					</dd><dt><span class="term"><i><tt>stacks</tt></i></span></dt><dd>
						The number of subdivisions along the Z axis.
					</dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glutSolidCone.3GLUT-description"/><h2>Description</h2><p>
			<tt>glutSolidCone</tt> and <tt>glutWireCone</tt> render a solid or wireframe cone respectively
			oriented along the <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll">
					<mml:mi>z</mml:mi>
				</mml:math> axis. The base of the cone is placed at <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll">
					<mml:mi>z</mml:mi>
					<mml:mo>=</mml:mo>
					<mml:mn>0</mml:mn>
				</mml:math>, and the top at <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll">
					<mml:mi>z</mml:mi>
					<mml:mo>=</mml:mo>
					<mml:mi>height</mml:mi>
				</mml:math>. The cone is subdivided around the <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll">
					<mml:mi>z</mml:mi>
				</mml:math> axis into slices, and along the <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll">
					<mml:mi>z</mml:mi>
				</mml:math> axis into stacks.
		</p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glutSolidCone.3GLUT-see_also"/><h2>See Also</h2><p>
